# Code Quality Rules

## General

- Always use Laravel Pint formatting (run `./vendor/bin/pint` before committing)
- Use type hints for all method parameters and return types
- Use PHP 8.1+ features: enums, named arguments, null coalescing
- Single quotes for strings unless interpolation needed
- Short array syntax (`[]`) always

## Architecture

- All models must have a Contract interface and Proxy class (Concord pattern)
- Use Repository pattern — never query models directly in controllers
- Events must follow `{domain}.{entity}.{action}.{before|after}` naming
- New packages go under `packages/Webkul/{PackageName}/src/`

## Security

- Always validate user input before processing
- Use `$fillable` on models, never `$guarded = []`
- ACL checks required for all admin routes
- Use parameterized queries (Eloquent handles this)

## Testing

- Write Pest tests for all new functionality
- Use `describe()` blocks to group related tests
- Use descriptive `it()` names
- Always include `beforeEach(fn() => $this->loginAsAdmin())` for admin tests
